                     <hi rend="largeCaps">FRANCIS DEANE</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18370130-696-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370130-696-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18370130-696-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>stealing, on the <rs id="t18370130-cd-181" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370130-696-offence-1 t18370130-cd-181"></join>24th of January</rs>, 280lbs. weight of lead, value 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18370130-name-1218" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1218" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1218" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1218" type="given" value="THOMAS BINGHAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370130-696-offence-1 t18370130-name-1218"></join>Thomas Bingham Richards</persName>; and fixed to a certain building; against the Statute, &amp;c.; and that Beale had been before convicted of felony.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370130-name-1219" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1219" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1219" type="surname" value="BRUSH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1219" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BRUSH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a gardener in the service of Mr. Thomas Bingham Richards at Battersea. On the 24th of January, at half-past twelve o'clock, I saw Deane handing something to Robert Beale, at the end of the Marsh-lane, Battersea—it appeared to be heavy—Beale took it across and put it into a donkey-cart, and Deane went towards Battersea—Beale and the cart towards the bridge—Mr. Richards has three empty houses there—the middle one has had the lead stripped off it—I have not compared this lead with the house—it was just in the front of the house I saw this done—in day-time—I could not see what the heavy article which was wrapped up was—there is about 2801bs. of lead taken from the premises.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370130-name-1220" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1220" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1220" type="surname" value="WELLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1220" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS WELLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my father-in-law, Samuel Eastman, a cow-keeper. I saw the prisoners near the house of Mr. Richards—I saw Deane go in and fetch lead out of the yard in a sack—he gave it to Beale, and he put it into a donkey-cart.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Deane</hi>. He says it was lead, and the other witness states it was wrapped up in a sack—how can he say what it was? <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> It was not quite covered up.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370130-name-1221" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1221" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1221" type="surname" value="HALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1221" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS HALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the two prisoners at Battersea-bridge, on the 24th of January.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370130-name-1222" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1222" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1222" type="surname" value="HARVEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1222" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HARVEY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 47.) I took some shoes off Deane's feet on the 24th, and compared them with some marks in the garden of Mr. Richards, they corresponded exactly.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370130-name-1223" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1223" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1223" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-1223" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM READ</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V 95.</hi>) I received information, and went in search of the prisoners, and apprehended Beale—I got some lead from inside the premises—it was not all taken away—there was no lead found in the cart.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Beale's Defence</hi>. In the morning, between nine and ten o'clock, I went over Battersea-bridge—I did not come back till five in the afternoon—I then heard of the robbery.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner Deane received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
